h3 Fieldset legend
p 
  | A Fieldset is used as a wrapper right inside the form element. Right after you define a fieldset, you can include a legend title. You can easily adjust the formatting of the fieldset and legend by changing the following variables in 
  code config/_forms.scss
  | :
p
  code $color-border-fieldset
  | Border color for the fieldset. (default: $color-brand-primary)
p
  code $color-background-fieldset-legend
  | Background color for the legend in the fieldset. (default: $color-white)

h6 Usage
pre
  code
    header HTML
    p
      = '<form>'
      br
      = '  <fieldset>'
      br
      = '    <legend> Legend </legend>' 
      br
      = '    <label>Input label'
      br
      = '      <input type="text" placeholder="Input placeholder....">'
      br
      = '    </label>'
      br
      = '  </fieldset>'
      br
      = '</form>'

h6 Example
.example
  form
    fieldset
      legend Legend
      label
        | Input label
        input type="text" placeholder="Input placeholder..."

h3 Labels
p You can show labels as inline or as block (default). To display the labels as inline you can put the label inside a different column to the left of the input. If you like the label to have an align to the right add a class of .label-right to the label. You can easily adjust the formatting of the labels by changing the following variables in 
  code config/_forms.scss
  | :
p
  code $color-label
  | Font color for the label. (default: $color-black)
p
  code $font-size-label
  | Fontsize for the label. (default: $font-size-default)
p
  code $line-height-label
  | Lineheight for the label. (default: $line-height-default)
